modules.description: Provides functions to resolve symbolic references in binary analysis, including lookup of symbols by name and mapping of addresses to symbol definitions. Works with symbol tables, address ranges, and identifier records. Used to trace function calls and data dependencies during binary disassembly.

Provides a mapping from stubs to their corresponding implementations in a BAP program, along with sets of stub identifiers and links to their resolved targets. Operates on BAP program terms, thread IDs, and associative maps. Used to analyze and resolve function call dependencies in binary analysis workflows.
